It's okay to forget things.

1768
02:34:49,250 --> 02:34:54,850
Many times, he would simply forget who or where he was.

1769
02:34:55,250 --> 02:34:56,850
There he is, he's up there on the roof.

1770
02:34:56,950 --> 02:34:58,650
It wasn't easy.

1771
02:34:58,750 --> 02:35:01,050
- Benjamin!
- I can see everything!

1772
02:35:01,150 --> 02:35:02,850
- I can see the big river!
- That's right,

1773
02:35:02,950 --> 02:35:04,750
you can see everything, sweetheart.

1774
02:35:04,850 --> 02:35:06,850
I can see the graveyard where Mama's buried,

1775
02:35:06,950 --> 02:35:10,250
- and all those other people.
- I want you to come down!

1776
02:35:10,350 --> 02:35:14,150
- What if I could fly?
- I knew a man who could fly.

1777
02:35:15,150 --> 02:35:18,050
You come down and I'll tell you all about him.

1778
02:35:21,650 --> 02:35:23,250
Somebody go up there.

1779
02:35:29,850 --> 02:35:32,850
He was five when I moved in.

1780
02:35:32,950 --> 02:35:37,350
Nearly the same age I was when I had met him.

1781
02:35:43,450 --> 02:35:47,350
"This is the picture of Old Man Kangaroo

1782
02:35:47,450 --> 02:35:49,850
"at 5:00 in the afternoon

1783
02:35:49,950 --> 02:35:53,450
"when he had got his beautiful hind legs."

1784
02:35:54,650 --> 02:35:55,950
The days passed.

1785
02:35:56,050 --> 02:36:00,350
And I watched as he forgot how to walk

1786
02:36:05,550 --> 02:36:08,050
- and how to talk.
- What's my name?

1787
02:36:08,450 --> 02:36:09,850
I'm Daisy.

1788
02:36:10,950 --> 02:36:12,750
Can you say "Daisy"?

1789
02:36:14,350 --> 02:36:19,550
In 2002, they put up a new clock in that train station.

1790
02:36:26,450 --> 02:36:30,150
And in the spring of 2003,

1791
02:36:34,550 --> 02:36:36,250
he looked at me

1792
02:36:38,750 --> 02:36:43,850
and I knew that he knew who I was.

1793
02:36:47,350 --> 02:36:53,150
And then he closed his eyes as if to go to sleep.

1794
02:37:25,750 --> 02:37:29,850
- I wish I'd known him.
- Now you do.

1795
02:37:34,350 --> 02:37:38,150
Mom, I think I should go see what's going on.

1796
02:37:45,250 --> 02:37:47,250
Good night, Benjamin.

1797
02:38:17,350 --> 02:38:20,250
Some people are born to sit by a river.

1798
02:38:21,750 --> 02:38:23,650
Some get struck by lightning.

1799
02:38:25,550 --> 02:38:27,650
Some have an ear for music.

1800
02:38:29,250 --> 02:38:30,950
Some are artists.

1801
02:38:32,250 --> 02:38:33,550
Some swim.

1802
02:38:35,050 --> 02:38:36,650
Some know buttons.

1803
02:38:38,450 --> 02:38:39,850
Some know Shakespeare.

1804
02:38:40,950 --> 02:38:42,750
Some are mothers.

1805
02:38:44,750 --> 02:38:47,750
And some people dance.

